RECEIVING INSPECTOR (JHB)
2023-09-29 - 2023-10-28
JHB000807
LOGISTICS, WAREHOUSE & FREIGHT
Gauteng, Kempton Park
(Market related)
Safair Operations, operating as FlySafair, has a vacancy for a Receiving Inspector (JHB) at our head office in
Bonaero Park. The successful applicant will report to the Manager: Warehouse.

RESPONSIBILITIES:
Receive shipments and sign paperwork upon receipt;
Unload packages from incoming trucks;
Uses dollies, forklifts, and other moving equipment to transport shipments from loading dock;
Checks shipping invoice to ensure all items are accounted for;
Opens boxes and inspect contents to ensure they are undamaged;
Verify packages according to order and invoices (quantity, quality, price etc.);
Maintain accurate records and assist in inventory control;
Contact procurement or shipper if a mistake is identified;
Work closely with the management team and Quality Assurance to resolve any queries or uncertainties;
Assume responsibility for returning unsatisfactory shipments or receiving replacements;
Packaging products for return to vendors and filling out any paperwork necessary;
Label deliveries and allocate them to their designated place;
Ensure invoices are signed and paid for satisfactory deliveries;
Stores, restocks, and shelves delivery items as necessary;
Track and report on all received spares daily (Properly accounting for the location of incoming goods);
Work with internal stake holders to resolve any problems;
Daily stock check on all items reflecting “received” on SAM;
Updating stock on the SAM system;
Managing tooling in the receiving area;
Ensures that the receiving area is clean and organized;
Processes transfers for shipments moving on to another location;
Ensuring all items are received correctly and not damaged during the shipping process.

REQUIREMENTS:
Matric;
Dangerous goods handling and Aircraft spares packing (Optional);
5 Years Warehousing or Receiving experience;
SAM AMO system (Optional);
Proficient in Microsoft Outlook and Excel.

PERSONAL ATTRIBUTES:
Immaculate time keeping;
Excellent communication skills both written and verbal;
Experience in operating forklifts;
Fundamental recording and basic math abilities;
Keen eye for detail;
Good physical condition;
Aptitude in decision-making and problem solving;
Organization;
Multitasking;
Flexibility.


APPLICATION GUIDELINE:
Suitable qualified candidates are invited to complete the prescribed form, available on our website: APPLY HERE
No external email applications will be accepted.
Should no feedback be provided within two (2) weeks from the closing date, please consider your application as unsuccessful.
FlySafair reserves the right
      * Not to proceed with this vacancy
      * To appoint the selected candidates based on its operational requirements.
Reference number – JHB000807

Preference will be given to members of under-represented designated groups.

For more information please contact: Lungiswa Hlathi

